OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773933104
OL,3,CWhy the Bank of England says inflation
OL,4,Cis rising again
OL,6,FTheir collective fear is possible
OL,7,F"second round" inflationary effects,
OL,8,Fthat is, a bidding up of wage
OL,9,Fsettlements even in today's relatively
OL,10,Fweak labour market.
OL,12,FSo written between pretty much every
OL,13,Fline in the minutes of the MPC rate-
OL,14,Fsetting meeting is the possibility
OL,15,Fthat interest rates will now have to
OL,16,Fbe increased before they resume a
OL,17,Fdownward trend.
OL,19,FFairly imminent interest rate cuts,
OL,20,Fwhich seemed likely before Trump's
OL,21,Fwar, are ruled out.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/4
